        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "We should be teaching students how to think, how to find reliable information, and how solve real-world problems using the tools that are available.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Instead, we trap them in a controlled environment and pretend that’s how the world works.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Like—I don’t know—asking them open-ended questions in real-time.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Letting them explain concepts in their own words.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Watching how they solve problems, and giving them the time and space to make mistakes, rethink, and try again.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "That’s",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "what school is for. Not regurgitating facts.",
